Analyze Your Data

Salesforce Analytics Tools

Reports and Dashboards

Manage Your Reports and Dashboards on Analytics Home

You can export report data to a spreadsheet.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To export reports:	Export Reports

When exporting a report... you can export an unlimited number of rows and columns. Most spreadsheet tools have row and column limits.
When exporting a report in Lightning Experience... you can export up to 100,000 rows and 100 columns.

Select an export view:
Formatted Report
Details Only

From the Reports or Analytics tab... click  and select Export.

If prompted, select a location and save the file.

Export a Report in Salesforce Classic
From Reports... click , and select Export.

Deselect “Don’t save encrypted pages to disk” under Internet options.

Select an encoding appropriate for your language.
Select the file type that you want to export to.
Click Export.
title: Exporting Reports in Salesforce
